This bird Pokémon is known for its voracious appetite and its unique way of catching prey. It's known to accidentally swallow things it didn't intend to catch.
It is a nocturnal Pokémon that only becomes active at night. Its favorite food is tree sap.
This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesn't like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.
Umbreon is the result of an Eevee's exposure to the moon's waves. It hides silently in darkness and waits for its foes to make a move. The rings on its body glow when it leaps to attack.

Fraxure are very combative and will not back down from a fight. They have incredibly long tusks that they use to tear apart opponents.

Mawile is a small, bipedal Pokémon with a steel-hard jaw and sharp teeth that can crunch through rocks.
Munna is a pink, nearly spherical, quadruped Pokémon of indeterminate species with four stubby legs and a body that swells in the middle.

Known as the ancestor of all bird Pokémon, Archen itself could not actually fly but moved by hopping from treetop to treetop.
A comparison revealed that Bidoof’s front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata’s.
There is a plant seed on its back right from the day this Pokémon is born. The seed slowly grows larger.

Cascoon makes its protective cocoon by wrapping its body entirely with a fine silk from its mouth. Once the silk goes around its body, it hardens. This Pokémon prepares for its evolution inside the cocoon.

Rayquaza is a large, green, serpentine creature. It has an elongated body and a nubby tail. It lives in the ozone layer, where it flies endlessly on the winds.
Electrode is known for its swift movements and explosive nature. Known as the bomb ball Pokémon, it has a tendency to explode with even the slightest of provocations.

Litten is a quadruped, feline Pokémon covered primarily in black and red fur.
Copperajah is a large, elephant-like Pokémon. It has a green hide with a hairless, light blue trunk and a single white tusk curving out of each side of its trunk.
Solgaleo is known as the beast that devours the sun. It radiates such a great light that it can light up the dark night.

Alcremie can produce whipped cream, which becomes richer the happier Alcremie is feeling. Desserts made using this cream are invariably delicious, so many pastry chefs strive to have an Alcremie as their partner.
Hariyama practices its straight-arm slaps in any number of locations. One hit of this Pokémon's powerful, openhanded, straight-arm punches could snap a telephone pole in two.
Lairon tempers its steel body by drinking highly nutritious mineral springwater until it is bloated. This Pokémon makes its nest close to springs of delicious water.
Cyclizar is a fictional Pokémon, therefore no official description is available.
When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

Slaking is a lazy Pokémon that lolls around for over 20 hours every day. Because it moves so little, it does not need much food. This Pokémon's sole daily meal consists of just three leaves. Its favorite move is Slack Off which allows it to heal up to half of its full HP.

Charizard is a draconic, bipedal Pokémon. It is primarily orange with a cream underside from the chest to the tip of its tail. It has a long neck, small blue eyes, slightly raised nostrils, and two horn-like structures protruding from the back of its rectangular head.
Dhelmise is a ghostly Pokémon that looks like a possessed anchor, wrapped in seaweed. It is known for its high attack stat.

Onix has a magnet in its brain. It acts as a compass so that this Pokémon does not lose direction while it is tunneling.
Gulpin has a voracious appetite. It can swallow something its own size whole.
Skitty has the habit of becoming fascinated by moving objects and chasing them around.
Doublade can carry out intricate attacks by telepathically coordinating its two blades to slash its enemies.
Yamper is a small, canine Pokémon. It tends to be very playful and chase after fast moving things, especially vehicles. Its body generates electricity, which it uses to its advantage in battles.

Marshadow is a mythical Pokémon that is known to be able to hide in the shadows of others.

Trapinch’s nest is a sloped, bowl-like pit dug in sand. This Pokémon patiently waits for prey to tumble down the pit. Its giant jaws have enough strength to crush even boulders.
Greavard's body is formed by shadows and fallen leaves. It is said to be the spirit of a lost child.
Kangaskhan carries a baby Kangaskhan in its pouch. The baby rarely ventures out of its mother's protective pouch.
Skarmory is entirely encased in hard, protective armor. This Pokémon flies at close to 190 mph.

Its poison seeps out from all over its body. It catches and eats its prey using its poison

Piplup is a Water type Pokémon introduced in Generation 4. It is known as the Penguin Pokémon. Piplup has a strong sense of self-pride. Because of its pride, it has a hard time accepting food from humans and often gets into fights over its territory.
It starts off battles by attacking with its rock-hard horn, but as soon as the opponent flinches, this Pokémon bites down and never lets go.
Scizor has a body with the hardness of steel. It is not easily fazed by ordinary sorts of attacks. It flaps its wings to regulate its body temperature.

It is based on the coelacanth, a group of lobe-finned fish which were believed to have been extinct until a living specimen was discovered in 1938.

Beautifly is a Pokémon species in Nintendo and Game Freak's Pokémon franchise. It resembles a brightly colored butterfly. Beautifly gathers pollen and nectar from flowers using its long, straw-like mouth.
Gabite has a dragon-like appearance with a large mouth full of sharp teeth. It is known to be very fast and agile.
Volcarona is a large, moth-like Pokémon with fiery wings. It is known for its powerful special attacks.
Froakie is a small, blue frog-like Pokémon. It is very agile and can jump high and far.

Buneary has brown eyes and a small, round, cream-colored muzzle. It has two types of fur covering its body: a light tan fleece that covers much of its lower body, feet, and the tips of its ears, and a smooth chocolate colored pelt on the upper half of its body.
Slowpoke uses its tail to catch prey by dipping it in water at the side of a river. However, this Pokémon often forgets what it’s doing and often spends entire days just loafing at water's edge.
Most of Meltan's body is made from liquid metal, and its shape is very fluid. It can use its liquid arms and legs to corrode metal and absorb it into its own body.
Kirlia uses the horns on its head to amplify its psychokinetic power. When the Pokémon uses its power, the air around it becomes distorted, creating mirages of nonexistent scenery.
Zarude can grow vines from the back of its neck, its wrists, and the soles of its feet at will. The vines are strong and flexible and are useful for many different situations.
Floatzel is a water type Pokémon known for its swift movements. It has a flotation sac that it inflates when it wants to float on water.
Pichu is an electric-type Pokémon. It is not yet skilled at storing electricity, and may send off sparks if it is amused or startled.
Zamazenta is a legendary Pokémon known for its heroic demeanor. It has a shield-like body to protect itself and its allies from any harm.
Known as a legendary Pokémon, Zacian has an attack power that surpasses all other Pokémon. It is said to be capable of slicing through anything with its sword.

column10: Evolves into Fletchinder at level 17, which evolves into Talonflame at level 35
column11: This tiny bird Pokémon is friendly and courageous. It makes up for its short wingspan with its fast speed, enabling it to dart around its enemies.
Combusken toughens up its legs and thighs by running through fields and mountains. This Pokémon's legs possess both speed and power, enabling it to dole out ten kicks in one second.
Furret has a very slim build. When under attack, it can slickly squirm through narrow spaces and get away. In spite of its short limbs, this Pokémon is very nimble and fleet.

Popplio's swimming speed is known to exceed 25 mph. It's better at moving in the water than on land. Still, when it's on land, it takes advantage of the elasticity of its balloons to perform acrobatic stunts and jumps.
This ancient bug Pokémon was altered by Team Plasma. They upgraded the cannon on its back.
Nickit are known to be cunning and stealthy, often creating distractions in order to steal from others.
Torracat has a bell-like object attached to its neck, which rings whenever the Pokémon uses an attack. It has a fierce and competitive nature.
Brionne learns dances by imitating the other members of its colony. It can perform dances perfectly after seeing them only once.
Crobat is a bat-like Pokémon with a high speed and attack.
Cradily is a plant-like Pokémon that is known for its high special defense and health.
Drapion is a scorpion-like Pokémon with a high defense and attack.
Skorupi is a scorpion-like Pokémon known for its high defense.
Cyndaquil protects itself by flaring up the flames on its back. The flames are vigorous if the Pokémon is angry. However, if it is tired, the flames sputter fitfully with incomplete combustion.

Scrafty has a very tough, ""hoodlum"" like personality. It can spit acidic liquid from its mouth, and its kicking power is formidable. Its skin is shed and draped around its waist like a pair of trousers, giving it a rough appearance.

Castform has a unique ability to change its form and type depending on the weather. It uses the power of nature to transform in order to protect itself. When it changes form, its body and eyes change color to match the weather.
Carvanha is a savage Pokémon that is known for its powerful jaw and aggressive nature. It has a body covered in blue scales and sharp fins. When it smells the scent of blood, it goes wild with rage.
It is a round, blue, amphibious Pokémon with a black, lumpy body underneath. It uses long-range ultrasonic waves that can generate earthquakes to deter predators.

Known as the ""Guardian of the Sea,"" Dragonite is capable of circling the globe in just over 16 hours. It is a kind-hearted Pokémon that leads lost and foundering ships in a storm to the safety of land.
Known as the Subterrene Pokémon, Excadrill can dig through the ground at a speed of up to 90 mph. It is a very powerful Pokémon with a strong affinity for digging and drilling.
A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil, Omanyte is believed to have been extinct for some 100 million years. It uses its tentacles to capture its prey.
Frillish, the Floating Pokémon. Frillish can sink its body into the sea to prevent detection by enemies, and it can absorb seawater, then project it from its body to sink ships and vessels.
Crustle, the Stone Home Pokémon. Crustle possess a large boulder on their back, which is actually a hardened shell. They are known to carry heavy loads uphill for many miles.
Xatu is known to stand still all day in one spot and stare at the sun unblinking. It has the enigmatic ability to see the future.

column10: Evolves from Sobble at level 16 and into Inteleon at level 35
column11: Drizzile, a water lizard Pokémon, has a habit of throwing tantrums, but it's so popular because it's cute when it's sulking.
Gossifleur prefers lands with clean water and air, and its pollen has a healing effect.
Moltres is a legendary bird Pokémon that has the ability to control fire.
Roselia shoots sharp thorns as projectiles at any opponent that tries to steal the flowers on its arms.
Spoink bounces around on its tail. The shock of its bouncing makes its heart pump. It carries a pearl from Clamperl on its head.

column10: Evolves from Snivy at level 17 and into Serperior at level 36
column11: It moves along the ground as if sliding. Its swift movements befuddle its foes, and it then attacks with a vine whip.

column10: Evolves from Charjabug when leveled up in a special magnetic field
column11: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.
This Pokémon came from the future by crossing over time. It is thought that so long as Celebi appears, a bright and shining future awaits us.

column10: Evolves from Sinistea when exposed to a Cracked Pot or Chipped Pot
column11: This species lives in antique teapots. Most pots are forgeries, but on rare occasions, an authentic work is found.
Krabby is a Water-type Pokémon known for its powerful pincers. It can be usually found on beaches, burrowed inside holes dug into the sand. It evolves into Kingler starting at level 28.

Graveler has a free-spirited nature and rarely stays in one place. It is known to climb up mountains and cliffs using only the power of its arms. Despite its rough, rocky appearance, it has a soft side for its friends.
Quagsire hunts for food by leaving its mouth wide open in water and waiting for its prey to blunder in unaware. Because the Pokémon doesn't move, it does not get very hungry.

column10: Evolves from Nidoran♀ starting at level 16, can evolve into Nidoqueen when exposed to a Moon Stone
column11: When Nidorina are with their friends or family, they keep their barbs tucked away to prevent hurting each other. This Pokémon appears to become nervous if separated from the others.

column10: Evolves into Marshtomp starting at level 16
column11: The fin on Mudkip’s head acts as highly sensitive radar. Using this fin to sense movements of water and air, this Pokémon can determine what is taking place around it without using its eyes.

column10: Evolves from Applin when exposed to a Tart Apple
column11: It ate a sour apple, and that induced its evolution. In its cheeks, it stores an acid capable of causing chemical burns.
Annihilape is a menacing figure with flames on its head and tail. It is known for its aggressive nature and powerful attacks.
Garbodor is a large pile of trash that has been brought to life. It uses its poisonous gas to attack and defend itself.

column10: Evolves from Tepig at level 17 and into Emboar at level 36
column11: Pignite is a bipedal pig-like Pokemon. It's known for its courageousness and powerful fire attacks.
Dunsparce is a serpentine Pokemon known for its ability to burrow underground. It is rare and difficult to find.
Venonat is a Bug/Poison type Pokémon introduced in Generation 1. Known as the Insect Pokémon, it is covered with a purple fur which is used to hide from enemies by blending in with the surroundings.

Gigalith is a blue, quadrupedal Pokémon, with various spiny, crystal-like red features jutting out of its body. Its limbs have gray joints and are topped with red crystalline features, with the two on its back forming an arch.
Miltank is a bipedal, bovine Pokémon which can produce highly nutritious milk.
Luxray is known for its glowing eyes that can see through anything, even walls. It's a very loyal Pokémon, often used by trainers to find lost things.
Stunfisk, the Trap Pokémon, conceals itself in the mud of the seashore, then it waits. When prey touch it, it delivers a jolt of electricity.
It is known to be extremely lazy, with its daily routine consisting of nothing more than eating, sleeping, and fishing.
They stick their spikes into cave walls and absorb the minerals they find in the rock.
If you get the feeling of being watched in darkness when nobody is around, Haunter is there.
It can dig through the ground at a speed of 30 mph. It could give a car running aboveground a good race.

column10: Evolves from Dusclops when traded holding a Reaper Cloth
column11: Dusknoir is known as the Gripper Pokémon. It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

column10: Evolves from Grotle starting at level 32
column11: Torterra is known as the Continent Pokémon. Ancient people imagined that beneath the ground, a gigantic Torterra dwelled.
Bellibolt is a  Generation VI Pokémon, known for its lightning-fast speed and high-voltage special attacks.
Introduced in Generation III, Minun is known as the cheering Pokémon. Its body is full of electricity, which it uses to cheer on its teammates in battle.

A Pokémon known for its high level of intelligence, and it can use its mental abilities to create a powerful force field. It can be a little timid, but it's a formidable opponent when it decides to fight.
Mantyke is a friendly Pokémon that loves to give people rides on its back. Despite its small size, it's very durable and can withstand a variety of attacks.
Boltund is known for its speed and agility. It can run faster than the human eye can track, and its electric attacks are powerful. It's a loyal Pokémon that will always follow its trainer's commands.

column10: Evolves from Azurill and can evolve into Azumarill
column11: Marill is a small, blue, bipedal Pokémon. It has a nearly spherical shape with a white belly, and has round ears with red insides.
Darkrai is a black, shadow-like Pokémon. It is known for causing people to have nightmares and has the ability to become a shadow and slip through cracks.

column10: Evolves from Swirlix when traded holding a Whipped Dream
column11: Slurpuff is a pink, bipedal, canine Pokémon with a sweet scent.
Solosis is a Psychic-type Pokémon. It uses psychic powers to communicate with telepathy, as well as to drive away potential threats.

column10: Evolves from Caterpie at level 7 and into Butterfree at level 10
column11: Metapod is a Bug-type Pokémon. Its shell is hard and it has a soft body inside. It is vulnerable to Fire, Flying, Rock and Ghost moves.
Bastiodon is known for its incredibly high defense and special defense stats, making it a sturdy wall in battles. Its body is covered in a durable, grey scale that can withstand powerful attacks.
Ariados is a dual-type Pokémon known for its ability to spin a web that can cover a tree overnight. Its high attack stat allows it to deal significant damage.
Dubwool is a sheep-like Pokémon with a fluffy and soft wool coat. It is known for its high defense stat, which, combined with its healthy HP, makes it a tough contender in battles.
Spinda is a unique Pokémon that has more than four billion possible patterns. Every Spinda's spot pattern is different, and it is known for its dizzying movements in battles.
Gyarados is known for its fierce temper and destructive nature. It has an impressive attack stat.
Tauros is a feisty Pokémon with excellent speed. Its powerful Tackle attack is feared among its opponents.
The leader of the Swords of Justice, Cobalion has a strong sense of justice and is known for its great defense and speed.

column10: Evolves from Gloom when exposed to a Sun Stone
column11: Bellossom is a Grass type Pokémon introduced in Generation 2. It is known as the Flower Pokémon. Bellossom gets its energy from sunlight and keeps on moving about actively in the daytime when it is warm. It spins its petals to scatter lots of pollen.
Minccino is a furry, white-bodied rodent-like Pokémon with long ears and a long, thin tail. It prefers clean habitats, and it is obsessed with cleaning dirty items.
Conkeldurr is a large muscular Pokémon with a nose resembling a trowel, which it uses to mix concrete. It is known to carry concrete pillars in its massive arms, which it uses to attack its enemies.
Ampharos gives off so much light that it can be seen even from space. People in the old days used the light of this Pokémon to send signals back and forth with others far away.

column10: Evolves from Tentacool starting at level 30
column11: Tentacruel has large red orbs on its head. The orbs glow before lashing the vicinity with a harsh ultrasonic blast. This Pokémon's outburst creates rough waves around it.
Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.
Adores circular objects. Wanders the streets on a nightly basis to look for dropped loose change.
It has a flotation sac that is like an inflatable collar. It floats on water with its head out.

column10: Evolves from Nidorina when exposed to a Moon Stone
column11: Nidoqueen's body is encased in extremely hard scales. It is adept at sending foes flying with harsh tackles. This Pokémon is at its strongest when it is defending its young.
Togedemaru is the Roly-Poly Pokémon with the capability to gather and store electricity from its surroundings. This Pokémon is known to roll into a ball to attack or protect itself.
